doc.previous: Fire protection within the city limits is provided by the Austin Fire Department, while the surrounding county is divided into twelve geographical areas known as Emergency Services Districts, which are covered by separate regional fire departments.[146] Emergency Medical Services are provided for the whole county by "Austin-Travis County Emergency Medical Services".[147][148]
after: The Texas Department of Transportation operates the Austin District Office in Austin.[150]
The Texas Department of Criminal Justice (TDCJ) operates the Austin I and Austin II district parole offices in Austin.[151]
